<head>
  <title>TimeEventGenerator</title>
</head>

<body>

    <h1>TimeEventGenerator</h1>

        <p>This is an event generator.</p>

    <h2>Description</h2>
        <p>This event handler generates time related events that other handlers can use for there time based actions.</p>


    <h2>Configuration</h2>
        <pre>
    &lt;eventInterface module='EventHandlers.TimeEventGenerator' name='TimeEventGenerator' latitude='51.5086' longitude='-0.1264' interval='seconds'&gt;
    &lt;/eventInterface&gt;
        </pre>
        <ul>
        <li>latitude - used in working out sunset and sunrise</li>
        <li>longitude - used in working out sunset and sunrise</li>
        <li>interval- either seconds or minutes</li>
        </ul>
        if latitude and longitude are not given default to London England. If you have no time based actions 
        requring second intervals then you can reduce the load on the WebBrick Gateway 
        computer by using minutes as the interval.

</body>

</html>
